Do you know Sulu from Star Trek? As a child he was sent to an internment camp with his family. So a WHOLE lot of people actually know a living human who was wronged by this decision made in the 1940's by our government. But I have a more difficult question to ask so I will give you as much time as you need to answer. Can anyone name an enslaved American that is alive today? The last person that was the GRANDAUGHTER of a slave died in 2015 at the supposed age of 116 years old. So by definition is would seem that the closest we can come to a living descendent of a slave would likely be a great, great, grandchild of a slave at the very best.

That is the difference between Japanese reparations vs. slavery reparations. There are still LIVING Americans that suffered from the internment of Japanese Americans. As far as African slaves none survive, no children survive, no grand children survive, and no great grand children survive. Unquestionably horrific things happened to African peoples in America 155 years ago under slavery. And yes crimes continued for a long time after in the form of people that were cruel and sometimes evil. Jim Crow laws that were both cruel AND evil.

Horrific things happened to the Jews, Armenians, and Bosnian people to name a few in the last 50 to 100 years. But how can you make reparations to the great great great grandchildren of the oppressed by having the great great great grandchildren who were not likely even descendants of the oppressors pay them? Perhaps we all need to move forward together and, while not forgetting past injustices, heal by being the people that Martin Luther King Jr envisioned. People that judge each other based on the quality of their character instead of the color of their skin.
